WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.840
ADINA: He's creating a virus
that will slaughter our people.

00:04.120 --> 00:06.240
You can stop it from happening.

00:06.320 --> 00:07.320
How?

00:07.760 --> 00:09.320
You have to kill him.

00:09.640 --> 00:13.120
She shares some of the same mutations...

00:13.200 --> 00:14.440
as the aliens.

00:14.920 --> 00:17.400
EMILY: It feels like
they're inside my head.

00:17.920 --> 00:18.920
Emily?

00:19.520 --> 00:21.160
-(GRUNTS)
-(GROANING)

00:22.960 --> 00:24.560
I'm looking for someone.

00:26.320 --> 00:28.840
Professor Bill Ward.

00:29.000 --> 00:31.240
This will terminate
the pregnancy in the first ten weeks.

00:31.320 --> 00:32.480
Have you told Nathan?

00:32.560 --> 00:34.680
No. It's better if he never knows.

00:37.000 --> 00:38.000
No!

00:38.080 --> 00:39.160
Come.

00:39.760 --> 00:41.480
(IN FRENCH) This is the building.

00:44.680 --> 00:47.000
SOPHIA: How do we find
this Professor Bill Ward?

00:47.080 --> 00:49.840
CATHERINE: We have to assume
he's some kind of scientist.

00:49.920 --> 00:52.400
(IN ENGLISH) Well, you said that
if you had a live alien,

00:52.480 --> 00:54.120
you could start testing the virus.

00:54.200 --> 00:55.640
Seems to me like you've got one.

00:58.200 --> 00:59.240
I'm sorry.

01:19.040 --> 01:21.320
-(EMILY BREATHING SHAKILY)
-(TAPPING SYRINGE)

01:24.640 --> 01:25.640
(SYRINGE JABBING)

01:35.280 --> 01:36.480
What's wrong with me?

01:40.880 --> 01:42.520
I-I don't know.

01:43.960 --> 01:46.600
Maybe you contracted
something on the ship.

01:51.360 --> 01:54.520
I'll check in on you later. Okay?

02:01.680 --> 02:03.920
-(BABY CRYING)
-(MAN AND WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

02:07.640 --> 02:08.840
SARAH: We just wanna see her.

02:09.160 --> 02:11.360
ZOE: I'm sorry. That isn't possible.
SARAH: She's our daughter.

02:11.480 --> 02:13.080
God, a few minutes.
That's all we're asking.

02:13.160 --> 02:15.400
Bill, she's refusing
to let us see Emily.

02:15.880 --> 02:19.960
Well, it might be for the best, Sarah,
until we figure out what's going on.

02:20.240 --> 02:22.400
-Have you seen her?
-Yes.

02:22.920 --> 02:25.040
-How is she?
-She's... She's okay.

02:27.560 --> 02:28.680
What are you gonna do with her?

02:29.240 --> 02:31.680
We'll hold her until
we're sure she isn't a threat.

02:32.840 --> 02:34.840
We'll leave. We'll take her away.

02:34.920 --> 02:36.800
You won't ever see us again.
I swear to God.

02:37.000 --> 02:39.680
-I'm sorry. That's not an option.
-JONATHAN: Why? Just let us take her.

02:39.760 --> 02:42.080
She... She did try to kill me.

02:43.920 --> 02:45.720
-Why would she do that?
-I don't know.

02:46.240 --> 02:50.320
-Some kind of brainwashing maybe.
-We don't know what they did to her.

02:50.480 --> 02:52.760
It's as much for
her protection as anyone's.

02:52.840 --> 02:55.760
-I just wanna see her. Please.
-I'm sorry.

02:56.680 --> 02:59.160
You have no idea
what it means to be a parent.

02:59.400 --> 03:01.400
I'm trying to keep you
and your family alive.

03:01.720 --> 03:05.240
Let's just figure out
what's best for Emily.

03:06.000 --> 03:09.480
I'll take great care of her. I promise.

03:20.600 --> 03:22.600
ZOE: Has the virus taken hold yet?

03:23.640 --> 03:25.320
She's getting sick.

03:25.960 --> 03:27.280
It's beginning to work.

03:27.960 --> 03:29.680
How soon until we know for sure?

03:31.320 --> 03:33.120
When her organs begin shutting down.

03:36.080 --> 03:37.520
She's gonna need insulin.

03:38.000 --> 03:39.800
I'll send Alex out to try and find some.

03:39.880 --> 03:40.960
Okay.

03:49.480 --> 03:51.440
(GROANING SOFTLY)

03:58.080 --> 03:59.080
(CROW CAWING)

04:29.040 --> 04:30.920
-(IN FRENCH) Where did you find this?
-NATHAN: In the foyer.

04:31.640 --> 04:32.720
Thank you.

04:37.240 --> 04:41.200
She hasn't really said anything
about the Colonel.

04:41.480 --> 04:42.600
(PAGES RUSTLING)

04:44.680 --> 04:45.680
Yeah.

04:45.760 --> 04:48.240
This is how she deals with things.

04:48.320 --> 04:50.320
She works.

04:51.680 --> 04:55.880
It was the same when our parents died.
She buried her head in books.

04:59.600 --> 05:00.920
And you?

05:02.240 --> 05:03.880
What did you do?

05:06.680 --> 05:09.440
I broke things and I punched people.

05:10.960 --> 05:13.480
When I was older,

05:13.560 --> 05:20.480
I had a lot of sex
and did a lot of drugs.

05:22.560 --> 05:23.640
(IN ENGLISH) Yeah.

05:26.680 --> 05:29.200
(IN FRENCH) What will you do
now you have lost Theo?

05:33.720 --> 05:36.600
I won't become that person again.

06:12.360 --> 06:13.480
(DOOR CREAKS)

07:01.160 --> 07:03.400
(WHISPERING) Kariem, watch the exit.

07:04.640 --> 07:05.720
Keep an eye.

07:26.520 --> 07:27.520
(METAL CLANGING IN DISTANCE)

07:30.480 --> 07:31.480
(CLANGING CONTINUES)

07:39.040 --> 07:40.120
Wait here.

07:44.120 --> 07:45.280
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

08:12.400 --> 08:14.160
Check the cupboards for insulin.

08:19.200 --> 08:20.200
(CLANGING CONTINUES)

08:32.480 --> 08:33.640
(CLANGING GROWING LOUDER)

08:41.640 --> 08:42.800
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

08:52.240 --> 08:53.240
(CLANGING CONTINUES)

09:11.240 --> 09:12.520
(CLANGING GROWS LOUDER)

09:37.160 --> 09:38.160
(RUSTLING)

09:41.080 --> 09:42.200
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

09:45.240 --> 09:46.240
(RUSTLING CONTINUES)

09:57.280 --> 09:58.280
(LOUD RUSTLING)

10:15.000 --> 10:16.440
Scarlet?

10:27.080 --> 10:28.160
Scarlet?

10:30.080 --> 10:31.080
Scarlet?

10:58.560 --> 10:59.640
Did you get it?

11:03.760 --> 11:04.840
What?

11:06.400 --> 11:08.280
-We lost someone.
-Who?

11:08.960 --> 11:11.240
A girl. Scarlet.

11:12.720 --> 11:13.800
They took her.

11:16.120 --> 11:19.560
-Why would they take her?
-I don't know.

11:30.160 --> 11:31.160
(BILL SIGHS)

11:34.640 --> 11:35.720
How's Emily?

11:36.440 --> 11:39.600
In and out of consciousness,
getting weaker all the time.

11:41.680 --> 11:43.360
The insulin will make her better?

11:44.720 --> 11:47.520
We have to see how the virus progresses
before we give it to her.

11:49.880 --> 11:51.920
We have to let her get really sick.

11:54.520 --> 11:55.520
(SIGHS)

11:59.640 --> 12:01.280
I know this is hard for you.

12:02.880 --> 12:04.840
I had to look into Sarah's eyes

12:05.800 --> 12:10.360
and lie
about what I'm doing to her daughter.

12:12.480 --> 12:13.480
(SIGHS)

12:13.560 --> 12:16.480
The virus is our only chance
of defeating them.

12:17.240 --> 12:19.160
I can put a gun to your head
and make you do it.

12:20.200 --> 12:22.520
-And then you can blame me.
-What age are you?

12:23.120 --> 12:25.360
-28.
-Jesus.

12:27.560 --> 12:29.360
You don't need to put a gun to my head.

12:48.360 --> 12:50.480
SOPHIA: (IN FRENCH)
Perhaps you should take a break?

12:52.200 --> 12:53.320
I'm fine.

12:56.480 --> 12:58.960
You are so not fine.

13:02.080 --> 13:03.160
Catherine.

13:12.840 --> 13:13.920
Catherine.

13:20.800 --> 13:22.600
-Stop.
-Why?

13:28.800 --> 13:29.880
(PAGES RUSTLING)

13:29.960 --> 13:31.920
It's okay to be upset, to cry...

13:32.560 --> 13:36.520
Why is everyone so obsessed with crying?

13:38.800 --> 13:41.040
Like if you sit around
crying all the time

13:41.120 --> 13:42.600
it makes you a better person.

13:44.520 --> 13:46.000
It achieves nothing.

13:47.040 --> 13:48.400
You cry if you want to.

13:52.160 --> 13:53.240
Okay.

14:37.720 --> 14:42.240
CATHERINE: Sophia. Sophia. Sophia.

14:53.600 --> 14:55.080
-I found him.
-Jesus.

14:55.240 --> 14:58.240
He's a professor of Neurogenetics at
the University of London.

14:58.400 --> 15:00.200
Don't do that to me.

15:01.160 --> 15:02.240
(EXHALES)

15:03.320 --> 15:04.320
(SIGHS)

15:06.280 --> 15:08.000
CATHERINE: We head towards Lyon...

15:08.440 --> 15:10.760
... then Dijon, north to Troyes ...

15:11.360 --> 15:13.000
... Reims, Arras...

15:13.560 --> 15:14.880
... then to Calais.

15:15.400 --> 15:16.800
When we're through the Channel Tunnel,

15:16.880 --> 15:18.360
it's about a hundred kilometres
to London.

15:20.400 --> 15:21.920
You can't be sure he's even alive?

15:22.760 --> 15:25.120
The guy at the observatory,
he told me he was alive.

15:25.200 --> 15:26.440
He said he had to be.

15:26.760 --> 15:29.680
You want to risk our lives on the
word of a half dead alien?

15:30.000 --> 15:31.120
Why would he lie?

15:31.320 --> 15:33.240
Maybe he wasn't lying.
Maybe he's just wrong.

15:33.400 --> 15:35.640
Maybe he was out of his mind.
You don't know.

15:35.720 --> 15:37.080
I believed him.

15:37.760 --> 15:39.400
It's hundreds of kilometres.
It's too dangerous.

15:39.680 --> 15:41.720
You think it's safe here?

15:42.160 --> 15:44.440
They came to the observatory
and killed everyone.

15:44.560 --> 15:45.640
They killed them...

15:45.720 --> 15:46.800
Catherine.

15:53.080 --> 15:55.560
He said that we could change everything.
That it wasn't too late...

15:55.640 --> 15:57.200
What does that even mean?

15:57.280 --> 15:58.560
I don't know.

15:59.400 --> 16:01.240
I think the answers are in here.

16:01.320 --> 16:02.320
This is crazy.

16:02.400 --> 16:04.080
What do you want to do? You're so smart.

16:04.160 --> 16:06.360
Maybe you want to wander
around with your rifle shooting them...

16:06.440 --> 16:09.600
... until you have no bullets left
and then they kill us.

16:09.680 --> 16:10.680
That's a great plan, genius.

16:10.760 --> 16:12.600
I want to keep you and Sophia safe.

16:12.680 --> 16:15.680
Maybe the best way to do that
is to go to London,

16:16.360 --> 16:19.240
...and find this guy and
actually try and do something!

16:19.320 --> 16:20.800
You're too stupid to see that!

16:24.120 --> 16:25.120
(FOOTSTEPS RECEDING)

16:28.880 --> 16:30.880
She needs this.

16:32.280 --> 16:34.480
You want to risk your life
because she needs it?

16:35.120 --> 16:36.120
Maybe.

16:37.240 --> 16:40.440
Yes. It's better than
risking your life for nothing.

17:23.680 --> 17:26.360
He's creating a virus
that will slaughter our people.

17:26.960 --> 17:27.960
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

17:39.520 --> 17:40.600
EMILY: Virus.

17:44.040 --> 17:45.440
You infected me.

17:52.280 --> 17:55.960
-You're going to kill them.
-They're gonna wipe us out.

17:57.160 --> 17:59.800
This is our only opportunity
to defeat them.

18:02.080 --> 18:03.560
Your wife wouldn't have wanted you
to hurt me.

18:03.840 --> 18:04.920
Helen's dead.

18:06.800 --> 18:08.280
And you did nothing to stop it.

18:11.680 --> 18:12.760
I tried.

18:17.600 --> 18:20.960
-It won't bring her back.
-You think I don't know that?

18:22.040 --> 18:25.400
-I made her a promise.
-You know it's wrong.

18:26.320 --> 18:27.640
You tried to kill me.

18:29.640 --> 18:31.480
Why don't you come down
off your high horse?

18:36.560 --> 18:37.640
(DOOR OPENS)

18:39.960 --> 18:40.960
(DOOR CLOSES)

18:51.120 --> 18:52.680
(IN FRENCH) Okay. We'll go to London...

18:54.400 --> 18:56.160
... and try and find this professor guy.

18:59.160 --> 19:00.600
Really?

19:01.160 --> 19:02.280
Yes.

19:03.560 --> 19:04.880
Thank you.

19:08.520 --> 19:11.680
You're not the only one
who's lost someone.

19:12.680 --> 19:14.240
You don't have to be a bitch about it.

19:27.280 --> 19:28.360
(SIGHS SOFTLY)

19:43.200 --> 19:44.200
(TUGGING)

20:01.680 --> 20:03.000
(CATHERINE GRUNTS)

20:10.680 --> 20:12.280
Give me the backpack!

20:13.400 --> 20:14.400
(GRUNTING)

20:20.120 --> 20:21.360
(ZIPPER OPENS)

21:09.960 --> 21:11.200
I'm sorry.

21:43.400 --> 21:44.520
(SHUSHING)

21:45.480 --> 21:46.760
(ENGINE RUNNING)

21:54.760 --> 21:56.000
CATHERINE: It's a car.

22:13.440 --> 22:14.680
Stay here.

22:14.760 --> 22:16.040
(ENGINE RUNNING)

22:41.520 --> 22:42.760
Shit.

22:43.520 --> 22:44.760
Open the door!

22:45.720 --> 22:46.840
(MAN COUGHS)

22:47.680 --> 22:48.920
Come on!

23:04.040 --> 23:05.120
(COUGHS)

23:08.520 --> 23:09.640
(ENGINE TURNS OFF)

23:14.080 --> 23:15.280
SOPHIA: Is he dead?

23:18.280 --> 23:19.680
(SCARLET BREATHING SHAKILY)

23:43.960 --> 23:44.960
(PANTING)

23:46.200 --> 23:47.360
(WHIMPERS)

23:52.320 --> 23:53.640
Hold this, hold this.

23:57.200 --> 23:58.600
-(WHIMPERING)
-Medic.

24:06.560 --> 24:07.600
Just breathe.

24:08.640 --> 24:09.640
(WHIMPERING)

24:12.600 --> 24:15.000
Why did they take you?

24:15.080 --> 24:16.200
(SOBBING)

24:17.960 --> 24:21.040
-Bill.
-What about him?

24:23.280 --> 24:26.640
They wanted to
know if he was still alive.

24:27.560 --> 24:29.960
-Why?
-I don't know.

24:33.480 --> 24:35.120
My stomach...

24:36.320 --> 24:37.400
(CRYING)

24:39.520 --> 24:41.560
WOMAN: It's okay, it's okay.
It's all right.

24:41.720 --> 24:44.120
MAN: What is that?
SCARLET: They drugged me.

24:44.920 --> 24:45.920
Okay.

24:46.000 --> 24:47.600
(SCARLET CRYING)

24:47.880 --> 24:49.280
WOMAN: I know, I know.

24:50.320 --> 24:51.440
MAN: There's something in there.

24:51.960 --> 24:54.120
-SCARLET: What is it?
-We need to cut you open.

24:54.200 --> 24:55.520
What? No.

24:55.600 --> 24:58.760
-Scissors.
-No, please. No. I don't wanna die.

24:58.840 --> 25:01.600
-No. Please.
-It's okay.

25:01.760 --> 25:03.480
It's okay.

25:04.600 --> 25:06.880
-(SCARLET SCREAMS)
-WOMAN: I know.

25:09.720 --> 25:10.880
It's okay. I know.

25:12.160 --> 25:14.960
SCARLET: Stop. No. Stop, please.
MAN: You're all right.

25:17.960 --> 25:19.440
It's some kind of metallic object.

25:20.680 --> 25:21.680
(SCARLET SOBBING)

25:23.200 --> 25:25.040
-Shit.
-(EXPLOSION)

25:33.480 --> 25:34.480
(HIGH-PITCHED RINGING)

25:36.640 --> 25:38.040
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

25:38.920 --> 25:41.080
(DISTORTED SHOUTING)

25:45.480 --> 25:47.480
-(COUGHING)
-(DISTORTED SHOUTING CONTINUES)

25:56.320 --> 25:57.400
ZOE: Bill.

25:59.120 --> 26:00.840
BILL: The virus.

26:01.360 --> 26:02.440
It's in the lab.

26:04.560 --> 26:05.560
Emily.

26:05.640 --> 26:06.680
(GUNSHOT)

26:09.840 --> 26:10.920
ZOE: Where are you going?

26:11.000 --> 26:12.000
-(GUNSHOT)
-(GRUNTS)

26:29.160 --> 26:30.160
(DOOR KNOB RATTLING)

26:33.280 --> 26:34.880
-(BILL COUGHING)
-(KEYS JINGLING)

26:35.640 --> 26:36.720
Open.

26:46.160 --> 26:47.160
Come on.

26:47.440 --> 26:48.920
You're okay, we've got you. Let's go.

26:49.640 --> 26:50.640
-(GUNFIRE CONTINUES)
-(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

27:05.000 --> 27:06.080
Jesus...

27:06.160 --> 27:07.240
Christ.

27:09.200 --> 27:10.280
Emily?

27:11.600 --> 27:13.280
-Is she okay? Is she okay?
-I don't know.

27:16.360 --> 27:17.920
-(MAN SCREAMS)
-(WOMAN SCREAMS)

27:24.880 --> 27:27.320
Go. Go. Go.

27:28.880 --> 27:29.920
(WOMAN SHOUTS)

27:33.880 --> 27:34.880
Go.

27:35.920 --> 27:37.080
(BILL COUGHING)

27:46.960 --> 27:47.960
(GUNSHOT)

27:48.640 --> 27:49.840
(WHIMPERING)

27:52.840 --> 27:53.960
(GUNSHOT)

27:59.280 --> 28:02.080
ADINA: Did you find Bill Ward?
ISLA: We checked all the bodies.

28:03.040 --> 28:04.120
He must have escaped.

28:05.440 --> 28:07.800
-And Emily?
-No.

28:29.600 --> 28:30.680
(CATHERINE SOBBING)

28:42.360 --> 28:43.600
(SOBBING CONTINUES)

28:51.480 --> 28:52.560
(SOBBING CONTINUES)

29:03.200 --> 29:04.280
(SOBBING CONTINUES)

29:17.960 --> 29:19.200
(CONTINUES SOBBING)

29:28.560 --> 29:29.920
(IN FRENCH) Are you okay?

29:30.560 --> 29:31.760
(SOBS)

29:33.040 --> 29:34.960
What's wrong?

29:40.400 --> 29:41.960
They killed...

29:43.520 --> 29:45.800
...the only man I've ever loved.

29:49.760 --> 29:51.920
I don't know how I'm supposed to feel...

29:53.200 --> 29:55.160
I don't know what to do...

30:04.160 --> 30:10.720
You feel like you want the world to end.

30:11.960 --> 30:12.960
Huh?

30:13.680 --> 30:16.000
What can I do?

30:16.520 --> 30:17.840
Nothing.

30:18.560 --> 30:20.000
All you can do is cry.

30:31.440 --> 30:32.680
(SOBBING)

31:32.520 --> 31:35.000
JONATHAN: Is she okay? Are you okay?

31:35.080 --> 31:37.080
SARAH: Em?
EMILY: I'm really cold.

31:37.200 --> 31:38.600
-Cold.
-SARAH: What's wrong?

31:39.040 --> 31:40.040
(EMILY BREATHING HEAVILY)

31:46.960 --> 31:48.040
Tell them.

31:50.680 --> 31:51.880
Tell them what you did to me.

31:57.160 --> 31:58.400
What's she talking about?

31:59.800 --> 32:02.480
-Tell them.
-What did you do?

32:10.000 --> 32:11.000
(EMILY SHUDDERING)

32:14.520 --> 32:15.600
Sarah...

32:20.120 --> 32:25.440
Emily shares some of the same
genetic mutations as... as them.

32:27.720 --> 32:31.280
I needed a live subject.

32:35.680 --> 32:37.920
-For what?
-To develop a virus.

32:39.360 --> 32:42.360
-A biological weapon.
-You made her sick?

32:44.320 --> 32:45.840
-You sick fuck...
-Whoa, whoa, whoa...

32:45.920 --> 32:47.320
How could you do that?

32:47.400 --> 32:50.800
BILL: I didn't have a choice.
They're going to wipe us out.

32:51.480 --> 32:55.440
I had to do something. I did it for you.

32:55.520 --> 32:57.320
I did it for Tom.
I did it for everybody.

32:57.560 --> 32:58.920
Fuck you, Bill!

33:01.920 --> 33:02.920
Mum, don't.

33:03.000 --> 33:05.680
SARAH: (SOBBING)
You experimented on my daughter.

33:05.760 --> 33:08.880
You don't understand, Sarah.
I had to do something.

33:08.960 --> 33:10.040
I trusted you.

33:10.840 --> 33:12.280
-Sarah.
-I thought you were my friend.

33:12.360 --> 33:14.560
-Come on, shoot him. Come on.
-Sarah.

33:16.240 --> 33:18.160
How would you feel
if someone did that to Helen?

33:18.880 --> 33:19.880
Huh?

33:21.000 --> 33:24.480
-Or Dan?
-At least they'd still be alive.

33:28.280 --> 33:29.280
Sarah.

33:40.760 --> 33:41.920
This is insulin.

33:43.840 --> 33:45.040
It'll make her better.

33:47.800 --> 33:53.360
If you ever touch my daughter again,
I will kill you.

34:04.840 --> 34:05.840
You okay?

34:18.600 --> 34:20.440
You need to be somewhere else.

34:35.840 --> 34:37.280
CATHERINE: (IN FRENCH) Thank you.

34:40.000 --> 34:42.680
We found you in your car.

34:46.520 --> 34:48.960
You should have left me.

34:51.080 --> 34:52.760
You've lost people?

34:58.760 --> 35:00.520
My whole family...

35:05.200 --> 35:08.120
My daughters were in Lille
during the attack.

35:09.200 --> 35:11.400
They never made it home.

35:12.640 --> 35:15.320
My wife was killed
about three months ago.

35:17.120 --> 35:18.960
Those things.

35:23.320 --> 35:25.680
My son died last week.

35:27.120 --> 35:30.400
The ones that look like us...

35:31.120 --> 35:33.960
We thought they were human.
We didn't know.

35:34.440 --> 35:36.360
They shot him.

35:40.680 --> 35:42.160
I'm sorry.

35:45.920 --> 35:47.200
(SIGHS)

35:48.960 --> 35:51.480
There didn't seem any point carrying on.

35:52.640 --> 35:53.640
(DOOR OPENING)

35:56.000 --> 35:58.080
CATHERINE: It's okay. They're with me.

36:11.480 --> 36:12.560
(DOOR CLOSES)

36:17.480 --> 36:19.640
This is my sister, Sophia.
And this is Nathan. Victor.

36:19.720 --> 36:21.400
-Hi.
-Hello.

36:22.960 --> 36:23.960
Hello.

36:25.880 --> 36:26.960
You want some wine?

36:29.080 --> 36:30.160
Yes, thank you.

36:44.000 --> 36:45.280
You okay?

36:47.600 --> 36:48.960
You've been crying?

36:57.760 --> 36:59.080
So have you asked him yet?

36:59.960 --> 37:01.400
What?

37:02.640 --> 37:04.720
Whether we can take his car?

37:05.960 --> 37:06.960
Sophia.

37:08.520 --> 37:10.040
How did you get it working?

37:11.480 --> 37:16.800
Old cars have less electrical circuits.
They can be repaired.

37:23.200 --> 37:25.440
We need to get to London.

37:26.400 --> 37:27.960
What's in London?

37:31.840 --> 37:32.840
Him.

37:40.720 --> 37:42.000
JONATHAN: Hey, found some lamps.

37:42.360 --> 37:44.920
-Where's Sacha?
-He's with Emily. Hey.

37:48.560 --> 37:50.720
What is this thing between them?

37:53.280 --> 37:57.560
I've heard the creatures won't hurt her,
just like they won't hurt Sacha.

37:59.120 --> 38:01.800
-Why is it just them?
-I don't know.

38:16.240 --> 38:17.480
The things I see,

38:20.000 --> 38:21.120
you see them too?

38:22.320 --> 38:23.920
I thought I was going crazy.

38:26.400 --> 38:27.760
Maybe we both are.

38:30.640 --> 38:35.080
All the time we were searching,
I knew I had to find you.

38:37.160 --> 38:41.280
When I saw you,
I couldn't believe it was you.

38:45.360 --> 38:46.440
JONATHAN: Hey.

38:48.200 --> 38:49.280
EMILY: Hey.

38:53.200 --> 38:55.520
Why don't you go
and give your mum a hand,

38:55.600 --> 38:57.520
see if you can find some stuff
to make some beds?

38:59.400 --> 39:00.920
I want to stay with her.

39:02.080 --> 39:03.840
JONATHAN: I think your mum
would really like it if you helped her.

39:07.880 --> 39:10.840
Go on. I've got this.

39:15.400 --> 39:16.440
How are you feeling?

39:18.880 --> 39:19.960
Better.

39:33.960 --> 39:39.040
It's some snacks. Chocolate, crisps.

39:56.720 --> 39:58.520
(STATIC CRACKLING ON RADIO)

39:58.600 --> 39:59.640
ZOE: Is anyone out there?

39:59.720 --> 40:00.880
(STATIC CRACKLING)

40:02.920 --> 40:04.160
Can anyone hear me?

40:04.240 --> 40:05.320
(STATIC CONTINUES)

40:10.760 --> 40:11.840
Here's some food.

40:13.760 --> 40:15.680
I'll see if I can find some painkillers.

40:15.920 --> 40:17.280
We lost the virus.

40:22.880 --> 40:25.600
It's in Emily. It's in her blood.

40:27.360 --> 40:29.240
We can still defeat them.

40:57.200 --> 40:58.400
EMILY: You can't sleep either?

41:21.680 --> 41:23.120
Why's this happening to us?

41:26.280 --> 41:27.360
I don't know.

41:32.800 --> 41:33.880
I'm glad you're here.

41:36.400 --> 41:37.760
It makes me feel better.

41:41.680 --> 41:43.760
-Probably sounds stupid.
-No.

41:48.640 --> 41:50.520
Emily, I feel like I know you.

41:53.280 --> 41:54.440
It's so strange.

41:55.520 --> 41:58.000
-It scares you?
-No.

41:59.720 --> 42:01.360
No one else understands.

42:05.200 --> 42:06.680
We have each other now.

42:08.840 --> 42:09.840
Hmm.

42:51.320 --> 42:53.600
(IN FRENCH) You can take my car.

42:57.920 --> 43:00.160
You should come with us.

43:00.960 --> 43:02.680
I think I'll stay.

43:06.920 --> 43:09.360
So you can blow your brains out
with a shotgun?

43:19.160 --> 43:20.800
Are you religious?

43:23.800 --> 43:24.960
No.

43:25.480 --> 43:26.640
I had faith.

43:31.520 --> 43:35.080
I believed there was a God.

43:36.080 --> 43:40.520
Even as my family died, I prayed.

43:42.440 --> 43:44.880
I prayed...

43:46.200 --> 43:48.720
... until there was no-one left
to pray for.

43:52.240 --> 43:55.000
What kind of God would let this happen?

43:56.720 --> 43:59.320
You're asking the wrong person.

44:00.360 --> 44:02.040
I'm a scientist.

44:02.600 --> 44:05.520
But now you're risking your life
to go to London...

44:05.600 --> 44:08.920
for reasons you don't
fully understand...

44:09.640 --> 44:13.280
because a man told you
he believed something?

44:13.920 --> 44:16.200
That's an act of faith.

44:18.520 --> 44:21.240
Maybe we all need a little faith now.

44:24.320 --> 44:25.560
Come with us.

44:27.200 --> 44:29.400
Maybe this is all part of God's plan.

44:31.000 --> 44:32.560
You don't believe that.

44:33.800 --> 44:35.880
You just don't want me to kill myself.

44:36.080 --> 44:37.080
True.

44:37.920 --> 44:39.720
I think that's a pretty good reason.

44:42.040 --> 44:43.360
Come with us.

44:44.480 --> 44:45.800
Please.

45:23.400 --> 45:25.760
I'm so sorry about Theo.

45:30.240 --> 45:34.200
How you were with him.
It made me so proud.

45:44.360 --> 45:46.320
What's he doing in there?

45:46.560 --> 45:48.480
Maybe he told us to wait outside

45:48.560 --> 45:50.680
so that he could finish what he started.

46:06.120 --> 46:07.120
(SIGHS)

46:29.120 --> 46:30.120
Thank you.

46:37.560 --> 46:38.680
(ENGINE STARTS)

46:54.440 --> 46:56.360
You like music?

46:58.280 --> 47:00.520
She hates music.

47:00.800 --> 47:02.400
I don't hate music.

47:02.680 --> 47:03.880
You never listened to it.

47:03.960 --> 47:07.400
That doesn't mean I hate it.

47:08.080 --> 47:10.120
Then this is for you.

47:10.480 --> 47:12.480
(DO YOU REALISE? PLAYING ON STEREO)

47:17.720 --> 47:19.720
(SONG CONTINUES AS SCORE)

47:19.800 --> 47:25.880
Do you realise

47:27.280 --> 47:32.360
That you have the most

47:32.440 --> 47:36.080
Beautiful face?

47:36.560 --> 47:40.360
Do you realise

47:46.840 --> 47:51.160
We're floating in space?

47:51.240 --> 47:55.440
Do you realise

48:00.040 --> 48:05.920
That happiness makes you cry?

48:06.000 --> 48:10.080
Do you realise

48:14.760 --> 48:20.040
That everyone you know

48:20.120 --> 48:24.040
Someday will die?
